      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "REOFFENDER (7) picked up where he left off the last campaign when he did some work from this barrier and dug deep for a fresh win at this circuit and distance on Monday. That stretched his winning run to six and he should strip fitter so can deliver again. SISTER PATRICK (3) is a talented mare who has put together four wins and one minor placing from five starts this campaign. Produced another fine effort last start when she came from wider and scored at this circuit and distance, coming in 2.8 metres ahead of her rivals. Should enjoy a nice run from this favourable starting position. Challenger. Tricky draw for ALDEBARAN MARCUS (11) but he comes into contention after racing wide but fighting well to score last start at this circuit and distance, his third success from his last five outings. TRANQUIL BILL (5) must be respected off a series of wins and placings, the latest offering a sound third behind REOFFENDER. Include.",
